Implementation details for P3.1 - AWS Cost Explorer Integration:

## Architecture Decisions
- Cost Explorer API only available in us-east-1, so CostTracker auto-switches region
- Uses UnblendedCost metric (actual costs) rather than BlendedCost
- Filters by 'agent-deploy:created-by' tag for total spend
- Filters by 'agent-deploy:deployment-id' tag for per-deployment costs
- Group-by functionality for cost breakdown by deployment

## Key Components Added
1. CostTracker - main struct wrapping costexplorer.Client
2. CostSummary - cost data with projections and alert flags
3. MonitoringReport - comprehensive spend report structure

## API Methods
- GetDeploymentCosts(ctx, deploymentID, start, end) - single deployment costs
- GetTotalMonthlySpend(ctx) - aggregate monthly spend
- GetCostsByDeployment(ctx, start, end) - grouped costs
- CheckAlerts(ctx, limits) - threshold/budget checks
- GetDeploymentsOverBudget(ctx, limits) - list overbudget deployments
- GenerateMonitoringReport(ctx, limits) - full report

## Testing Strategy
- Unit tests for calculation logic (projectMonthlySpend)
- Alert threshold boundary testing
- Budget utilization percentage calculations
- Structure/field validation tests
- Integration tests would require AWS credentials (not included)

